org.dexpi.pid.xml

Class ObjectAttributesReference

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dexpi.pid.xml.ObjectAttributesReference

  • public class ObjectAttributesReference
extends java.lang.Object

    Java-Klasse für anonymous complex type.

    Das folgende Schemafragment gibt den erwarteten Content an, der in dieser Klasse enthalten ist. 

     <complexType>
   <complexContent>
     <restriction base="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}anyType">
       <choice minOccurs="0">
       </choice>
       <attGroup ref="{}ItemReferenceGroup"/>
       <attribute name="DependantAttribute" use="required" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
       <attribute ref="{}DependantAttributeContents default="ValueAndUnits""/>
     </restriction>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

    • Method Detail

      • getContent

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getContent()
        Gets the value of the content property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the content property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getContent().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list String
